The paper focuses on the application of deep learning to a tactile sensor for robot touch, which is a topic within the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning specifically for image processing and edge detection is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV), and the paper applies these techniques to the tactile sensor. Additionally, the use of deep learning for generalization and robustness is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE).
